-- Bobcats Fire Coach Paul Silas After Finishing NBA-Worst 7-59
-- B y   S c o t t   S o s h n i c k
-- 2012-04-30T19:05:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/bobcats-fire-coach-paul-silas-after-finishing-nba-worst-7-59.html
The Charlotte Bobcats fired coach
Paul Silas after the team finished a National Basketball
Association-worst 7-59 this season, setting a record for lowest
winning percentage.  Silas had a record of 32-88 after taking over the Michael
Jordan-owned team in 2010. The Hornets in a statement said the
search for a replacement would begin immediately.  Silas has a career record of 377-531 over 11 seasons with
the Clippers, Hornets, Cavaliers and Bobcats.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Soshnick in New York at 
 ssoshnick@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  